# opened files of process id

+unix +lsof +pid +file

/Users/michal/Documents/journal/zettel/20220107184947-watch-log-file-unix
/Users/michal/Documents/journal/zettel/20210804194151-unix-file-fifo-pipes

You might want to check files opened by a given process. Here is how to do it
with PID:

```sh
lsof -p 416
```

The `-p` flag lets you find a process by its PID.
